## Conceptual Summary
Recursion Theory explains cognition as a **self‑referential dynamic system**.  
It integrates:
- recursive loops (behavior)  
- recursive attractors (stability)  
- recursive failure modes (breakdown)  
- recursive repair (restoration)  

Together, these documents form a complete model of how recursive cognition evolves, stabilizes, destabilizes, and recovers.

---

